# ============================================================
# [*synapse-diagnose] COMMAND:
#   0. Run SYNAPSE diagnostic report comparing expected vs actual pipeline
#   1. Execute: node -e "const {runDiagnostics}=require('./.aiox-core/core/synapse/diagnostics/synapse-diagnostics');console.log(runDiagnostics(process.cwd()))"
#   2. Display the full markdown report to the user
#   3. Highlight any FAIL or WARN items that need attention
# ============================================================
COMMANDS_RULE_SYNAPSE_DIAGNOSE_0=Run SYNAPSE diagnostic report comparing expected vs actual pipeline state
COMMANDS_RULE_SYNAPSE_DIAGNOSE_1=Execute the diagnostics module and display the full markdown report
COMMANDS_RULE_SYNAPSE_DIAGNOSE_2=Highlight FAIL and WARN items with recommended fixes
COMMANDS_RULE_SYNAPSE_DIAGNOSE_3=Check hook registration, session state, manifest integrity, pipeline layers, and UAP bridge

# ============================================================
# [*analyze-external-repo] COMMAND:
#   0. Deep comparative analysis of external git repos against AIOX
#   1. Analyze squads/, agents/, skills/, workflows/, tasks/, workers/, infrastructure/
#   2. Create side-by-side comparison tables with recommendations
#   3. Identify NEW CAPABILITIES, ENHANCEMENTS, and AIOX ADVANTAGES
#   4. Provide implementation roadmap with effort estimates
# ============================================================
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_0=Deep comparative analysis of external git repos vs AIOX
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_1=Analyze all directories: squads, agents, skills, workflows, tasks, workers, infrastructure, packages, memory, constitution, data, templates, tests, docs, .claude
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_2=Create side-by-side comparison tables: Feature | External Repo | AIOX | Recommendation
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_3=Identify novel patterns as NEW CAPABILITY with priority and effort estimate
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_4=Identify improvements as ENHANCEMENT with exact file paths and line numbers
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_5=Identify missing AIOX patterns as AIOX ADVANTAGE
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_6=Document technology stack differences and compatibility considerations
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_7=Create detailed implementation roadmap with dependencies and ordering
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_8=Provide handoff document ready for developer implementation
COMMANDS_RULE_ANALYZE_EXTERNAL_REPO_9=NEVER skip any directory—be exhaustive and complete in analysis
